# 2. 思わぬ救世主

Ichika: Good morning...
Ichika: Oh, no one else is here yet. I might've left home a little too early.
Ichika: But I've hit a bit of a wall with my song, so it might be nice to work on it somewhere else for a change...
Ichika: Still... Why am I having so much trouble...?
Ichika: (I'm currently writing a song with a message about helping others when they need it, but... No matter how many times I try, it ends up sounding off...)
Ichika: (I've even tried adjusting the parts of the melody that I thought needed fixing... But that hasn't really led to an improvement in quality.)
Ichika: (Also... I'm trying to get used to digital tools, but it isn't going well. I can't quite get the melody that's in my head...)
Ichika: This is a lot harder than I realized...
Ichika: (But I want Miku to sing my song... I've come this far already, so I need to at least finish it.)
Ichika: Still... What do I do in these situations? I remember Saki saying...
Saki: Let's get started, everyone! It's time for Ms. Saki's songwriting seminar!
Rin: Woohoo!!!
Luka: Oh, what's going on here?
Honami: Ichika was asking about how to become a better songwriter, and these two became so excited...
Saki: Alright, Ichi! Once again, ask me anything you like!
Ichika: O-Okay, Ms. Saki.
Miku: She's even calling her “Ms. Saki” like she's a teacher.
Shiho: What are you two doing...?
Ichika: S-So... What do you do when you get stuck while writing a song? Do you have any advice regarding that?
Saki: Ah, excellent question. Many things can cause you to get stuck while writing a song...
Saki: For example, if you're having trouble producing the sound you want despite having a solid image in your head, you may want to try looking at your song objectively by taking a step back.
Ichika: Objectively?
Saki: Working on a song for too long can cause you to become unable to distinguish between what's good and what's bad!
Saki: So, whenever you find yourself in such a situation, my... Ms. Saki's advice to you is to try listening to the song you're working on using different headphones or somewhere else entirely.
Saki: By doing that, you might figure out what you were missing and get the hint that you need!
Ichika: I never would've thought to do either of those things... Thank you very much for your advice, Saki.
Saki: You're welcome! And never stop learning!
Saki: Alright, to be fair, I'm still pretty new to songwriting and also keep getting stuck...!
Ichika: Listening to it somewhere else entirely...
Ichika: This might be the perfect place... I think I'll try that while I wait for the others to arrive.
Ichika: Let's see... Just plug the cable into my phone and press play...
Miku: ♪————
Ichika: Oh wow... The studio's speakers sound so much cleaner... This sounds completely different compared to when I listen to it on my computer...!
Ichika: But...
Ichika: The melody still sounds off... It's not capturing that feeling of wanting to help someone who's in need...
Ichika: If anything, these speakers are only making the problems more evident...
Ichika: The bass sounds...thin... The drums sound light too. It's like everything sounds really far away...
Ichika: It's not just the melody. I can see now that I need to also be careful about which sounds I choose... The issues are just piling up...
???: What song is this?
Ichika: Huh...?
Ichika: H-Honami?! When did you get here?!
Honami: Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to scare you. I should've let you know that I was here...
Ichika: I-I'm also sorry. My back was to the door, so I didn't see you come in.
Honami: No, that's okay. More importantly, this song... Is that Miku singing?
Ichika: Oh... So, um...
Honami: But I've never heard this song before. It skipped in a few places, and the melody seems unfinished...
Honami: Ichika... Did you write this...?
Ichika: Oh...
Ichika: Yes, actually...
Honami: I knew it...! You were still trying to write your own song. Not only that, you're having Miku sing it...!
Ichika: B-But I really just started working on it. I mean, I can't write anything amazing like Saki!
Ichika: I feel bad about making Miku sing such a half-baked song, and...
Ichika: I'm having a lot of trouble. Using digital tools to write songs is so hard.
Honami: Oh, you mean using a computer to write music? That's very different from how we usually produce songs...
Honami: Especially since you have to choose which instruments to use and what sounds they're going to make. It sounds tough...
Ichika: Yeah... I know what kind of song I want to write and have been inputting sounds based on how we usually play...
Ichika: But I'm not getting what I want. I even realized just now that my song has all these other problems with it.
Ichika: I thought I'd be able to help the band more if I learned to write songs for us...
Honami: Ichika...
Honami: What if you asked Ms. Yoisaki? She composes songs using digital tools...
Ichika: Oh...
Ichika: That's right. I remember her mentioning that before.
Ichika: Thanks, Honami! I'll try contacting her right away.
Honami: Hehe. I sure hope she can help.
Saki: Morning! You two are here pretty early!
Shiho: You know you could've gotten started without us, right? Wait, why's only this speaker on...?
Ichika: Oh... Th-The person who used it last must've forgotten!
Saki: Yeah, that is pretty common! I remember going out and leaving the air conditioner on during summer once, Tsukasa turned into a popsicle the moment he got home!
Shiho: I feel like the temperature setting you chose is more the issue.
Ichika: Honami, would you mind keeping my song a secret from the others until I've had a chance to finish it...?
Ichika: Partly because it's embarrassing, but mostly... I want the song to be complete when they hear it.
Honami: Hehe. Okay, I promise not to tell them. And I'll help you when I can to make sure it turns out well.
Shiho: Good job today, everyone.
Saki: Bye bye, Ichi!
Ichika: Okay... Another day, another good practice.
Ichika: We even got to finalize our decision to make videos moving forward.
Saki: So, which song should we do a video for first?!
Shiho: We'll need to choose carefully. Our first video's probably gonna leave the biggest impression about who we are.
Ichika: Right... Those who like our first video might become interested in us and even come to see us live.
Honami: Then, why don't we choose a song that we all feel good about and serves as a nice representation of who we are...?
Honami: In other words... It'll be Leo/need's way of introducing itself to the world.
Saki: Yeah! You said it perfect, Hona!
Ichika: A song that we all feel good about and serves as a nice representation of who we are... I guess that means...
Ichika, Shiho & Honami: Saki's song! The song Saki wrote!
Saki: Whoa! You all landed on the same answer!
Ichika: It seems like the right choice for our first video since we practiced so much just to play it during that show.
Shiho: Yeah, I agree.
Shiho: And it means something special to me. All of you working hard to master it compelled me to play with everything I had...
Ichika: Shiho...
Shiho: S-Saki, is that okay with you?
Saki: Of course! I can't believe it'll be our first video... I mean, I worked super hard on it, so this makes me really happy♪
Honami: Hehe. For now, until we do our shoot, let's keep practicing.
Ichika: Unlike shows, videos last forever... And that comes with a different sort of anxiety...
Ichika: I'll need to practice a lot for it.
Ichika: Hm? Did someone just send me a message?
Ichika: Oh...!
Honami: Hello, Ms. Yoisaki. Thank you for having me over again today.
Kanade: Thank you for coming again, Ms. Mochizuki. Also...
Kanade: Welcome, Hoshino.
Ichika: Thank you for agreeing to help me today. After I suddenly asked you to teach me about digital music tools too...
Ichika: Not only that, you even invited me to your house. I feel kind of bad about all of this...
Kanade: It's my pleasure. I mean, I happen to have the equipment you need for this.
Kanade: Oh, however, the house may be a bit of a mess since Ms. Mochizuki hasn't had a chance to clean it yet...
Honami: Hehe. Don't worry. It'll be clean in no time.
Kanade: Thank you...
Honami: So, if you'll excuse me, I'll get started.
Honami: Good luck, Ichika. And thank you again, Ms. Yoisaki. I hope you two can make some good progress.
Kanade: Me too. Anyway, shall we head up to my room...?
Ichika: Yes!
